DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       Reads  a GRASS raster map as input.  Calculates textural features based
       on spatial dependence matrices for north-south,  east-west,  northwest,
       and  southwest directions using a 3x3 neighborhood (i.e., a distance of
       1).  Writes to standard output.  Be sure to carefully set your  resolu-
       tion  (using  _g_._r_e_g_i_o_n)  before running this program, or else your com-
       puter could run out of memory.  Also, make sure that  your  raster  map
       has no more than 255 categories.

